- lightweight,open-source application development framework(pre-written code)
- framework of frameworks
	eg. Struts,Hibernate
- variants of Springs are Spring MVC,Spring Boot, Spring Security
- DI and IoC allow us to create large scale & loosely-coupled applications

Advantages:
1. Plain Old Java Object(POJO)
	- makes the applications lightweight

2.Modularity
	- IoC allow us to reuse components throughout the application without manually
	  creating/managing dependencies

3. Strong support for Java
4. Scalable Transactions
5. Secure

Feature
1. IoC

2. Aspect Oriented Programming(AOP)

3. Dependency Injection

4. MVC

5. Error Handling